What a great experience. Being Brooklyn born and raised my mind boggled at the thought of going to a CHAIN PIZZERIA. However, we had an awesome server, Anthony. Great seats in the back where it was quiet and we got to watch them setup their Christmas tree. The octopus was tender and delicious. The calamari melted in your mouth. The baked clams were cooked to perfection. And the margherita pizza was some of the best I've ever had. If you're looking for an out of town experience without having to leave town, Patsy's is a perfect choice.

This weekend my family and I gathered at Patsy’s for a repass. Let me tell you one thing, it was an amazing experience! From the fresh out the oven hot bread all the way down to the homemade marscapone cheesecake, it was all delicious. The restaurant itself has a warm inviting fun atmosphere, beautifully decorated! The staff, unbelievably attentive and we never had to ask for anything twice let alone once, they were on top of their game! We could literally taste the freshness in all of the entrees. We have to say a big thank you to the manager Arnold, he was attentive, friendly and over all just a pleasure to deal with. There is no doubt about it that we will be back whether it is another event or just a night we’re looking for fresh hot delicious food! Thank you Patsys for having us! We’ll be back!

My family and I thoroughly enjoyed the food at Patsy's. We started with several appetizers consisting of the calamari, mozzarella sticks, fried zucchini sticks and the fried cod. Needless to say we all enjoyed each one of these immensely. Our main courses consisted of the rigatoni with meatballs, spaghetti and meatballs, and the rigatoni with the bolognese sauce. Their Bianca pie was also delicious. We ended this meal dessert of their freshly-made tiramisu.  Recommend this restaurant very highly.

We had a Pizza party at Patsys Bay Ridge on Tuesday August 6th, the service was fantastic, the waitress was unbelievable, we were twenty, Everything was wonderful, from the moment we arrived, could not have asked for a better experience! The pizza was the best, served several different kinds, not a complaint from any of the ladies! When we approached Arnold, the manager, he said they had never had an adult pizza party, but he put on one that had all the ladies talking about the best pizza they had, watch out Arnold, we will be back! Thanks for an enjoyable afternoon, not one complaint! Arnold your the best!🤗

Look -- the pizzas are phenomenal. Legitimately very very good. 5/5 for the pizzas alone, but unfortunately they do serve other food and it is pretty damn ghastly. I gave their meat ragu pasta a try about three months ago and was severely underwhelmed, so I thought I'd try the in house dining experience again and ordered the special, a squid ink risotto with calamari. What I got was some kind of barebones risotto (no cheese no peas no mushrooms or onions, just the arborio and squid ink) with deep fried squid rings just tossed on top. It was. I don't even know how to explain it, but truly and profoundly disappointing on so many different levels, especially for $25. Don't get me wrong, the wine portions are plentiful, the service is attentive, but for the love of God don't order anything but pizza here. Ever.

Food was delicious, staff was great. So accommodating. I called at the last minute on Friday evening looking for a restaurant for dinner after the Circus. When I called I was told they'd be happy to have the 18 of us. I had already purchased a small cake along with cupcakes for my great niece's 11th birthday. I asked if I could bring and was assured it would be fine. Upon our arrival, they brought the car and cupcakes to the refrigerator, brought it out on platters along with plates and forks & candles. Service with a smile. Again, great staff, good food, we had such a nice time. We live in Massachusetts, so the next time I'm in Brooklyn will be eating at Patsy's!

I live in Bay Ridge and I am so happy that this place opened up. I am a fan of Patsy's as I have been to the original location in Spanish Harlem back in the 90's. And I have been to several locations ever since. So today was my first visit to this Patsy's which by the way opened up 7 weeks ago. I didn't even know that there will be a Patsy's in Bay Ridge. In any event, I discovered it and I was quite pleased with my experience. I love the decor and the ambience of this place. It is very nicely designed. The pizza is exactly what I am used to when it comes to Patsy's. I highly recommend this place and you know I'll be coming back!!
Amazing service!!! Amazing food!!! Amazing atmosphere!!! A must!!! I highly recommend it!!!!
This place is a great new addition to Bay Ridge! And it looks great
Patsy's is Open everyday including Sunday We are closed on Tuesdays.

I visited this place with my fiance  this evening. Overall  we had a great experience. I was greeted at the door by a gentleman named Charlie. He was very  welcoming and sat us immediately in the back of the restaurant. The server was nice she brought our drinks out quickly and took the  order. Our appetizers came out first Clams, Polipo Salad & cold antiposto and were very delicious.  After that we had a pizza alla vodka and it was  good!! The atmosphere was just right, the place look great. They even had a beautiful long bar in the front of the restaurant. I would definitely recommended this place to anyone to go solo, on a date, go with a group of people or even grab a drink. Plus I found out that  you can rent the back room out for parties.

To be fair, this restaurant hasn't been open a week as of this review.  I was not impressed with the pizza, I felt that it was average. There are other places very close by that you can order similar pizza by the slice.  The ceaser salad dressing had anchovies in it, which was unexpected and unappreciated. It reminded me of eating tuna salad, not a salad that was lettuce and cheese.  I'm sure that over time the food will improve.
